Regenerate Codex cache without drift workarounds

Codex 0.142.0 drifted away from the committed cache: it defaults to
gpt-5.5, prefers a WebSocket transport, and reads AGENTS.md from
within the project tree (and the global ~/.codex/AGENTS.md) rather
than the filesystem-root /AGENTS.md the prepared image wrote.  The
stale cache was kept alive by a hard-coded legacy-key alias table
and a synthesized WebSocket upgrade probe.

Remove both workarounds and fix the root causes instead:

- Drop `model` from the OpenAI cache key and strip the injected
  <environment_context> turn (cwd, workspace root, timezone, date)
  so the key depends only on the prompt and survives Codex upgrades
  and different checkout paths.
- Inject the rumpelpod system prompt into ~/.codex/AGENTS.md, which
  Codex loads globally, so it reaches the model in a single turn.
- Point the codex tests at a custom model provider with
  supports_websockets = false so Codex uses the HTTPS transport the
  cache proxy speaks, and drop the `-m o3` model override.

Regenerate the llm-cache/codex responses against Codex 0.142.0.
